.TH "gpiod_hog" 9 "gpiod_hog" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
gpiod_hog \- Hog the specified GPIO desc given the provided flags
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" gpiod_hog
.BI "(struct gpio_desc *desc "  ","
.BI "const char *name "  ","
.BI "unsigned long lflags "  ","
.BI "enum gpiod_flags dflags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "desc" 12
gpio whose value will be assigned
.IP "name" 12
gpio line name
.IP "lflags" 12
bitmask of gpio_lookup_flags GPIO_* values - returned from
\fBof_find_gpio\fP or \fBof_get_gpio_hog\fP
.IP "dflags" 12
gpiod_flags - optional GPIO initialization flags
